{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform Child Maintenance Service: Support Active Fathers & End Historic Arrears",
        "additional_details": "Some are being chased for historic arrears they never had a chance to challenge, pushing some families into hardship and damaging the very children the system is meant to protect.\r\n\r\nWe\u2019re calling for change.\r\nThe CMS must:\r\n\r\nRecognise shared parenting in its calculations.\r\nAllow fair reviews and appeals of old debts.\r\nWrite off unfair or unaffordable historic arrears.",
        "background": "The CMS is meant to support children - we think that too often, it\u2019s tearing families apart. We feel that many loving, active fathers are treated unfairly & that the CMS ignores shared parenting, fails to recognise time spent with children, & can create unaffordable debt that parents can\u2019t dispute.",
